    "title": "Manipulating Reality Composer scenes from code"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Although ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " behaviors provide a way to add interactivity to your",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scene without writing code, there are times when the only way to implement functionality",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is to make changes from code. You can manipulate the objects in your scene in many",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "different ways, including hiding or duplicating them, or changing their location,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "orientation, and scale.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Access-scene-objects",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Access scene objects",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To retrieve specific objects from a scene, first assign each object a name in Reality",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Composer, using the Properties inspector. If you give an object a unique name, Xcode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "automatically creates an accessor property during code generation. For example, if",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you have an object called Steel Box in a scene named Box that’s contained in a file",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "called ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Experience.reality",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", you can get a reference to that object by using code",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "if let boxScene = try? Experience.loadBox() {",
            "    let box = boxScene.steelBox",
            "    // Do something with box.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you give multiple objects in a scene the same name, the generated property returns",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "an array containing all of the objects that share that name.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you need to load a named object without using generated code, such as when working",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "with downloaded reality files or loading objects created at runtime, you can use",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Scene/findEntity(named:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function on the scene entity.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "if let boxScene = try? Experience.loadBox() {",
            "    if let box = boxScene.findEntity(named: \"Steel Box\") {}",
            "        // Do something with box",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Hide-and-show-entities",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Hide and show entities",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In addition to hiding and showing objects in your scene using behaviors, as described",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/bringing-a-reality-composer-scene-to-life",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", you can also use code to hide",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and show them, by using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/isEnabled",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property. If you set",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "an object’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/isEnabled",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/false",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ",",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "ARKit doesn’t render it and it doesn’t participate in the scene’s physics simulation.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If you set it back to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/true",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ARKit",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "starts rendering the object again and it resumes participating in the physics simulation.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Child objects of the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/isEnabled",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " property inherit its",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "settings, so disabling ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/isEnabled",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " also disables all of its children.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Transform-a-scene-object",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Transform a scene object",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can transform (move, rotate, or scale) objects in a scene by using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/transform",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "property of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To move an object, change the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Transform/translation",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " value of the transform.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, to move a scene object 10 cm along the x-axis, use this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "myEntity.transform.translation += SIMD3<Float>(10, 0, 0)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Similarly, to scale an object, modify the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Transform/scale",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " of the entity’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/transform",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, you can double the size of an object in your scene like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "myEntity.transform.scale *= 2"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To rotate an object, make changes to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Transform/rotation",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of its ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/transform",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". This code shows you how to rotate an object",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in your scene by 90° on the z-axis:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "// Calculate 90° as radians.",
            "let radians = 90.0 * Float.pi / 180.0",
            "",
            "// Create a quaternion that represents a 90° rotation on the z-axis",
            "// and add it to the existing rotation value.",
            "anchorEntity.transform.rotation += simd_quatf(angle: radians, ",
            "                                              axis: SIMD3<Float>(0,0,1))"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Clone-an-entity",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Clone an entity",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you need to create multiple copies of the same object at runtime, avoid loading",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the entity multiple times, which can cause performance issues. Instead, load a single",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "copy of the entity before you need it, but don’t add it to your scene. When you need",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a new instance, call the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity/clone(recursive:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function on the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "loaded entity, and then add the clone as a child of a scene anchor.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Here’s an example of cloning an anchored entity and adding it to your ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ":",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let copy = myEntity.clone(recursive: true)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-force-to-an-object",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add force to an object",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If an object in a scene participates in the physics simulation, you can add force",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to that object from code by using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ModelEntity/addForce(_:relativeTo:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "method. Provide a vector representing the amount and direction of force to add to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the object as the first parameter. Here’s an example of applying force to an object",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to make it fly away from the camera:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "// Adjusting the forceMultiplier value changes the amount of force applied.",
            "let forceMultiplier = simd_float3(repeating: 10)",
            "ball.addForce(simd_float3(x: cameraForwardVector.x,",
            "                          y: cameraForwardVector.y,",
            "                          z: cameraForwardVector.z) * forceMultiplier,",
            "              relativeTo: nil)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
